PROJECT TITLE:
Full-Stack MERN Multi-Product Delivery Website (Food, Drinks & Cooking Gas)

PROJECT OVERVIEW:
Build a production-ready full-stack MERN (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js) web application for a delivery business selling food, beverages, and bottled cooking gas.

IMPORTANT:
- In current frontend code, bottled gas is labeled as "fuel".
- Replace all references of "fuel" with "gas" consistently across the entire system (frontend + backend + database).

The system must include:
- Client-facing interface
- Admin dashboard (/admin route)
- Secure authentication
- Full backend integration
- Real-time inventory tracking
- Payment integration (MTN & Airtel)
- Role-based access control

--------------------------------------------------
TECHNOLOGY STACK (MANDATORY)
--------------------------------------------------

Frontend:
- React.js
- Tailwind CSS
- Framer Motion (for animations)
- Axios for API calls
- React Router DOM

Backend:
- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB with Mongoose ORM

Authentication:
- JWT-based authentication
- bcrypt for password hashing

File Storage:
- Cloudinary or local file upload system

Payments:
- MTN Mobile Money integration
- Airtel Money integration

Architecture Requirement:
- Separate folders for:
  - controllers
  - routes
  - models
  - middleware
  - utils
- Use RESTful API structure:
  - /api/auth
  - /api/products
  - /api/orders
  - /api/users
  - /api/admin

--------------------------------------------------
FRONTEND REQUIREMENTS (DO NOT ALTER DESIGN)
--------------------------------------------------

CRITICAL RULE:
Maintain the EXACT current frontend design and layout.
Do NOT redesign or restructure UI.
Only connect it to backend logic and ensure full functionality.

Requirements:
- All existing buttons must function correctly.
- All forms must submit real backend data.
- Shopping cart must work properly.
- Order tracking must work visually.
- Maintain responsiveness across all devices.
- Implement loading states for all API calls.
- Display user-friendly error messages.
- Use toast notifications for actions (success/failure).
- Use Framer Motion for smooth animations.
- Implement optimistic UI updates where applicable.

--------------------------------------------------
USER ROLES & PERMISSIONS
--------------------------------------------------

1) CLIENT:
- Register
- Login
- Browse products
- Filter by category (Food, Drinks, Gas)
- Add to cart
- Place order
- Track order
- View order history
- Update profile

2) ADMIN:
- Secure login
- Access /admin dashboard only
- Manage products (Create, Read, Update, Delete)
- Manage clients (View, Edit, Suspend)
- View all orders
- Update order status
- Monitor active users
- View analytics overview (basic stats)

--------------------------------------------------
DATABASE STRUCTURE REQUIREMENTS
--------------------------------------------------

Collections Required:

1) Users
- name
- email
- phone
- password (hashed)
- role (client/admin)
- last_login
- isActive (boolean)
- suspended (boolean)
- createdAt

2) Products
- name
- description
- category (food | drinks | gas)
- price
- stock
- image
- createdAt

For GAS products:
- cylinderSize (6kg, 12kg, 20kg, 25kg)
- purchaseType (Refill | New)
- availabilityStatus

3) Orders
- userId (reference)
- items (productId, quantity, price)
- totalAmount
- paymentMethod (MTN | Airtel)
- paymentStatus
- orderStatus
- deliveryAddress
- createdAt
- updatedAt

--------------------------------------------------
ACTIVE CLIENT LOGIC (STRICT DEFINITION)
--------------------------------------------------

Define "Active Client" as:

A user who:
- Has logged in within the last 7 days
OR
- Has an ongoing order that is NOT marked as Delivered or Cancelled.

System Requirements:
- Automatically update last_login on every login.
- Automatically compute activity status.
- Store and update activity status in database.

Admin Dashboard:
- Show green circle indicator + "ACTIVE" label on active clients.
- Show different visual indicator for inactive clients.

--------------------------------------------------
ORDER STATUS FLOW (MANDATORY)
--------------------------------------------------

Order lifecycle must follow this structure:

- Pending
- Confirmed
- Out for Delivery
- Delivered
- Cancelled

Rules:
- Admin can update order status.
- Clients can visually track order progress.
- Status updates must reflect in real-time (or near real-time via refresh).

--------------------------------------------------
ADMIN DASHBOARD REQUIREMENTS
--------------------------------------------------

Route:
- /admin

Features:
- Overview statistics (total users, total orders, total revenue)
- Client management table
- Product management table
- Order management section

Client Management:
- View all clients
- Filter active clients
- View client details page
- Edit client
- Suspend client

Client Detail Page Must Show:
- Full contact information
- Order history
- Current orders
- Total purchases
- Activity status indicator (green circle if active)

--------------------------------------------------
PAYMENT INTEGRATION
--------------------------------------------------

Integrate:
- MTN Mobile Money
- Airtel Money

Requirements:
- Secure payment verification
- Store transaction reference
- Update paymentStatus accordingly
- Prevent order confirmation without successful payment

--------------------------------------------------
SECURITY REQUIREMENTS (STRICT)
--------------------------------------------------

- Hash passwords using bcrypt
- JWT must expire (set expiration time)
- Protect all /admin routes with role-based middleware
- Validate and sanitize all inputs
- Prevent unauthorized API access
- Handle errors securely (no stack traces in production)
- Use environment variables for secrets

--------------------------------------------------
INVENTORY MANAGEMENT
--------------------------------------------------

- Reduce stock automatically after order confirmation.
- Prevent ordering if stock is insufficient.
- Real-time inventory updates.
- Admin can update stock manually.

--------------------------------------------------
GENERAL DEVELOPMENT RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Do NOT break existing frontend structure.
- Connect frontend to backend via clean REST APIs.
- Ensure full integration between frontend and backend.
- Ensure clean, readable, maintainable code.
- Use proper error handling.
- Follow best practices for scalability.

--------------------------------------------------
FINAL EXPECTATION
--------------------------------------------------

Deliver a fully working production-ready MERN application where:

- All frontend features function correctly.
- Authentication works securely.
- Admin dashboard is fully operational.
- Payment integration works.
- Orders flow correctly through lifecycle stages.
- Active client system works accurately.
